features: D3+K2 - BETTER TOGETHER: On their own, Vitamins D3 and K2 are essential micronutrients, but together, they're an essential team. Vitamin D3 helps your body absorb calcium, while vitamin K2 directs calcium to your bones instead of joints and arteries, where too much calcium could be problematic. Not that's teamwork!

PLANT BASED: Our Vitamin D and K supplement for women and men contains vegan D3 (cholecalciferol) from lichen and K2 from fermented chickpeas with added Coconut MCT Oil for enhanced absorption. This two-in-one super supplement is 100% free of animal ingredients and encapsulated in the first carrageenan-free plantgel softgel.

ONE-A-DAY FORMULA: Get the best of both worlds with Sports Research D3+K2. Just one easy-to-swallow veggie softgel provides 125cg (5000iu) of Vegan & 100mcg of Vitamin K2 (as MK7, the form of K2 with the highest bioavailability) for stronger bones and immune system support so you can shine your brightest.*

QUALITY TESTED: We hold all of our supplements to a higher standard. Our K2 with D3 vitamin supplement is Vegan Certified, Non-GMO Project Verified, and free of unwanted fillers, carrageenan, gluten, and soy. Each batch is third-party tested for quality and manufactured in the USA in a cGMP-compliant facility.

THE SPORT OF LIFE: Founded in Southern California in 1980, Sports Research is a family-owned business born from a passion for fitness and wellness. Our goal is to embrace the sport of life through research-backed products created for every body—inside and out.

The Vitamin D3+K2 softgels used to be white/clear. Why do they now appear orange? In 2022 we added a new, natural color protectant to the outer shell of our Vitamin D3+K2 softgels to protect the ingredients inside against photo-degradation from light and UV exposure. The active ingredients have not changed in our formula. Is the Vitamin D3 made from lanolin? No, our Vitamin D3 is made from lichen, a plant-based source of Vitamin D3. Is this product Kosher or halal certified? What type of gelatin is used? Our Vitamin D3+K2 is not certified Halal or Kosher. However, we use plant-based tapioca gelatin in our softgels containing NO bovine (beef), porcine (pork), or carrageenan. Where is this product sourced from? Is it really Vegan-friendly? All product ingredients are vegan-friendly and come from plant-based sources. Our K2 as MK7 is from fermented chickpeas, our D3 is from lichen, and our MCT oil is from Coconut. Is this product soy free? Our product is the only non-GMO project verified, soy, gluten, and animal free D3+ K2 available. Additionally, our K2 is sourced from chickpeas and not soy like most K2 products.
